# Generated by wallust from the current wallpaper — do not edit by hand.
# Included via `config-file = ?wallust` in ~/.config/ghostty/config.
#
# Hybrid scheme: the background and cursor follow the wallpaper (so the
# terminal still tints to match and stays transparent), while the 16 ANSI
# colors and a bright foreground are pinned to a fixed vivid palette
# (TokyoNight). This keeps neofetch/ls/syntax colorful and text readable on
# every wallpaper, including dark or near-monochrome ones.

